From: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Jan 2013 12:46:51 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 046/122] MIPS: Don't select SYS_SUPPORTS_HOTPLUG_CPU for
 CPU_CAVIUM_OCTEON

Source: Cavium Networks, Inc.
MR: 00000
Type: Integration
Disposition: Merged from Octeon Tree
ChangeID: 38d094aa9f9024fd69b6cc9a75cb91f2e1e0981c
Description:

It breaks rebooting (and suspend probably doesn't work either).

Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Leonid Rosenboim <lrosenboim@caviumnetworks.com>
Signed-off-by: Corey Minyard <cminyard@mvista.com>
[Original patch taken from Cavium SDK 3.1.1 525]
Signed-off-by: Bin Jiang <bin.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/Kconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/Kconfig b/arch/mips/Kconfig
index 95fa1f1..6af2583 100644
--- a/arch/mips/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/Kconfig
@@ -2554,7 +2554,7 @@ config ARCH_HIBERNATION_POSSIBLE
 
 config ARCH_SUSPEND_POSSIBLE
 	def_bool y
-	depends on SYS_SUPPORTS_HOTPLUG_CPU || !SMP
+	depends on (SYS_SUPPORTS_HOTPLUG_CPU || !SMP) && !CPU_CAVIUM_OCTEON
 
 source "kernel/power/Kconfig"
 
